    "Some additional information and summary statistics are reported in Appendix B.",
    "There are three layers in the U.S.",
    "Federal Court system: the local level (District Court), intermediate level (Circuit Court), and national level (Supreme Court).",
    "Federal judges (numbering roughly 180 in circuit courts and 680 in district courts) are appointed by the president, conrmed by the Senate, and serve with life tenure.",
    "They are responsible for the adjudication of disputes involving common law and interpretation of federal statutes."
